  "response_text": "A woman stands at a kitchen sink in a warm, wood-cabinet kitchen, wearing a plaid shirt and a blue patterned headscarf. The double sink in front of her is full of standing, murky water. Dishes are stacked at the left, a blue sponge lies on the counter, and a metal bucket sits to the right with a long-handled utensil inside it. Beside the bucket is a red, white, and blue container that appears to be a crystal drain opener. The woman looks frustrated and busy as she uses a small metal saucepan like a dipper, scooping water out of the clogged sink and dumping it into the bucket.\n\nThe commercial then focuses on a white bottle labeled “Liquid-plumr.” Its cap is off, and the bottle is tipped downward over a sink. The label has large red lettering and a blue starburst that reads “Pours through standing water.” A clear stream pours from the bottle into the standing water below, splashing and rippling across the sink basin. The stream continues steadily toward the drain area. A close view of the drain appears with the word “LATER” printed in bold black letters beneath it, suggesting time has passed.\n\nThe scene changes to a bathroom. An older bald man in a blue-and-white collared shirt leans over a white bathtub filled with cloudy standing water. A Liquid-plumr bottle sits on the tub ledge near the faucet, and a yellow sponge rests nearby. Yellow towels hang in the background above pale cabinets. Like the woman in the kitchen, he is bailing water with a metal saucepan, dipping it into the tub and lifting it out while bracing one hand on the tub edge. He looks annoyed and weary as he continues trying to clear the water manually.\n\nThe product demonstration returns: the white Liquid-plumr bottle is again tipped over a sink, pouring a clear liquid into standing water. The liquid flows in a smooth stream from the open mouth of the bottle and lands in the water, creating spreading ripples and small bubbles. The view shifts into a stylized transparent drain demonstration. A pale stream passes down through a layer of water toward the drain opening, then continues into a clear vertical pipe beneath the sink. Inside the pipe, bubbles and cloudy movement appear around a dark clog near the bottom, showing the product traveling down through water to reach the blockage.\n\nThe bathroom drain appears again with the bold word “LATER” beneath it, then the older man is shown still by the bathtub, tipping the metal saucepan as if emptying it and then setting it down. The product demonstration repeats once more, with Liquid-plumr pouring from the white bottle into standing water at the sink. The liquid stream falls cleanly into the basin, rippling the water around the drain.\n\nThe commercial ends on a clean sink with two Liquid-plumr containers standing upright beside the drain: a smaller bottle in front and a larger handled jug behind it. Both have the same white-and-orange label with red “Liquid-plumr” lettering and a blue starburst. Large black text appears to the left of the bottles, filling much of the sink area: “Just pour it in and it works.”",
